abstract: The Michael Cohen show wasn’t pretty. But it is what the country needs.
snippet: The Michael Cohen show wasn’t pretty. But it is what the country needs.

abstract: Members of a more centrist coalition of Democrats say that instead of single-payer health care, Congress should initially focus instead on shoring up the Affordable Care Act.
snippet: Members of a more centrist coalition of Democrats say that instead of single-payer health care, Congress should initially focus instead on shoring up the Affordable Care Act.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Denouncing the profit motive in health care, more than 100 House Democrats rallied on Wednesday around a bill to replace most private health insurance with a national single-payer system, “Medicare for all.”

abstract: Mr. O’Rourke said he would make an announcement “soon.” There has been much speculation about his possible entrance into the 2020 race.
snippet: Mr. O’Rourke said he would make an announcement “soon.” There has been much speculation about his possible entrance into the 2020 race.
lead_paragraph: Beto O’Rourke, who has turned his consideration of a presidential campaign into an online version of reality television, inviting Americans to follow along through journal dispatches as he travels the country in search of personal clarity, said Wednesday that he had made his decision.

abstract: The first legislative proposal of the year on the subject could help shape the terms of the debate.
snippet: The first legislative proposal of the year on the subject could help shape the terms of the debate.
lead_paragraph: The basic idea of “Medicare for all” is that all Americans should get access to the popular, government-run program. But a new bill toward this goal, the first introduced in the current Congress, would also drastically reshape Medicare itself.

headline_main: What Would ‘Medicare for All’ Do to Medicare?

abstract: Maybe older is better. Just look at Nancy Pelosi.
snippet: Maybe older is better. Just look at Nancy Pelosi.
lead_paragraph: Dianne Feinstein doesn’t get it. How could she? She’s 85. Ancient. She has had too many decades to resign herself to the status quo, and she won’t be around to watch the fires rage and the oceans boil. Step aside, Granny. Sturdier legs will lead the way.

abstract: In a blow to the campaign, the consultants, who produced some of the most memorable ads in 2016, said that they had strategic differences with Mr. Sanders and his wife.
snippet: In a blow to the campaign, the consultants, who produced some of the most memorable ads in 2016, said that they had strategic differences with Mr. Sanders and his wife.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The architects of the 2016 insurgent campaign for Senator Bernie Sanders abruptly parted ways with his 2020 campaign on Tuesday, dealing him a surprise blow one week after he entered the presidential race with an emphatic show of fund-raising strength.

abstract: Is it time for the U.S. to confront other great powers — or to retreat?
snippet: Is it time for the U.S. to confront other great powers — or to retreat?
lead_paragraph: In the past several months, a meaningful debate has finally started to emerge over America’s role in the world. Politicians and analysts — left, right and center — are conceding that longstanding mistakes have brought the United States to an uncertain moment. Provoked by President Trump, they are concluding that the bipartisan consensus forged in the 1990s — in which the United States towered over the world and, at low cost, sought to remake it in America’s image — has failed and cannot be revived.
